## Field Descriptions

### user.message
**CRITICAL**: Save the **COMPLETE** user message, word-for-word.
- ✅ DO: Save exactly what user typed
- ❌ DON'T: Summarize, paraphrase, or truncate
- If message is very long (>2000 chars), still save it all

### ai.message  
**CRITICAL**: Save the **COMPLETE** AI response, including:
- All explanations and reasoning
- All code snippets (with ```language markers)
- All examples and comparisons
- All suggestions and next steps

**Format**: Plain text with markdown formatting preserved

**Example**:
```
"message": "让我分析一下现有的系统消息实现...\n\n经过查看 UnifiedMessageTypeConverter.java,我发现:\n\n```java\npublic String matchMessageTypeByValue(int value) {\n    // 如果msgType不在映射表中\n    // 会直接使用Backend的MsgType名称\n    return backendMsgTypeName;\n}\n```\n\n这说明...[完整分析]...\n\n因此我建议采用您提出的方案:1个subMsgType + 2个contentKey,原因如下:\n1. 更简洁...\n2. 更易维护...\n\n具体实现方式:\n```java\n// Scenario 1\noutMsg.setContentKey(\"channel_system_blocked_cannot_invite\");\n```\n\n这样修改后...[完整说明]..."
```

### ai.keyPoints
Brief bullet points (5-10 items) summarizing what AI did in this turn:
- Analyzed which files
- Found what insights
- Made what recommendations
- Generated what code

### ai.codeSnippets
Array of code snippets that AI **analyzed or referenced** (not generated):
- `language`: Programming language
- `file`: Source file name
- `purpose`: Why this code was shown (e.g., "Analyzed to understand...")
- `snippet`: The actual code (can be multi-line)

### ai.fileChanges
**CRITICAL**: Detailed record of **every file modification**:

#### Structure
```json
{
  "operation": "edit | create | delete",
  "file": "path/to/file",
  "purpose": "Why this change was made",
  "changes": [
    {
      "type": "addition | deletion | modification",
      "section": "Which section of the file",
      "description": "What was changed",
      "linesAffected": "140-145",
      "contentBefore": "Previous content (if deletion/modification)",
      "contentAfter": "New content (if addition/modification)"
    }
  ],
  "diffSummary": "High-level summary of net changes",
  "toolsUsed": ["edit_existing_file", "create_new_file"]
}
```

